WEBVTT

00:04.038 --> 00:06.274
[ Man ]
One, two! One, two, three!

00:29.696 --> 00:31.699
[ Ducks Quacking ]

00:35.636 --> 00:37.304
Go get it, boy!
Ruff!

00:40.707 --> 00:44.578
So, Leela,
how about a romantic ride
in one of those swan boats?

00:44.677 --> 00:47.581
They're kinda dangerous,
but I finally mastered them.

00:47.680 --> 00:50.151
Those aren't swan boats.
They're swans.

00:50.250 --> 00:52.552
Oh. That explains
these boat eggs.

00:52.652 --> 00:54.621
[ Whirring ]
[ Gasps ]

00:56.624 --> 00:59.560
[ Screaming ]

01:02.429 --> 01:04.331
Aaah!

01:04.432 --> 01:06.334
Mmm! Hmm.

01:06.433 --> 01:08.936
Aaah!
[ Gasps ]
Aaah!

01:21.814 --> 01:24.317
Pitiful ballplayers of Earth.

01:24.418 --> 01:27.019
I am Ethan "Bubblegum" Tate,

01:27.120 --> 01:29.989
Commander of
the Harlem Globetrotters.

01:30.090 --> 01:32.426
- [ Gasping ]
- For generations,

01:32.526 --> 01:36.364
your puny planet
has lived in peace with
the Globetrotter home world.

01:36.463 --> 01:38.998
But now, for no reason,

01:39.098 --> 01:41.301
we challenge you
to defend your honor...

01:41.402 --> 01:43.304
on the basketball court.

01:43.403 --> 01:46.539
-[ Commotion ]
-Will no one meet our challenge?

01:46.640 --> 01:49.810
Have none of you
pathetic Earthlings game?

01:49.909 --> 01:52.146
- What happens if we lose?
- Nothing!

01:52.246 --> 01:54.647
There is nothing at stake
and no threat...

01:54.747 --> 01:57.218
beyond the shame of defeat.

02:01.322 --> 02:04.992
[ Gasps ]
This will not stand!

02:05.091 --> 02:09.163
[ Murmuring ]
I'll take you on,
you air-balling bozos!

02:09.263 --> 02:11.164
You, old man? Hmph.

02:11.264 --> 02:13.700
Sweet Clyde,
laugh derisively at him.

02:13.800 --> 02:18.038
[ Laughing ]

02:18.138 --> 02:20.039
I may be an old man--

02:20.139 --> 02:22.342
in fact,
I'm fairly sure I am--

02:22.443 --> 02:25.679
but I'll put you Globetrotters
in your place...

02:25.778 --> 02:28.716
with my team
of mutant atomic supermen!

02:28.816 --> 02:31.551
[ Cheering ]
Irie, Professor!

02:32.586 --> 02:36.656
Behold,
my mutant atomic supermen!

02:38.658 --> 02:41.027
They're only a foot high,
Professor.

02:41.127 --> 02:45.498
Well, they're still young--
mere atomic superboys, really.

02:45.598 --> 02:47.567
We'll need to
speed up their growth...

02:47.668 --> 02:50.503
with time particles
called chronitons.

02:50.603 --> 02:53.507
Aren't those the particles
that destroyed an entire
civiliza--

02:53.606 --> 02:58.378
Good news, everyone!
You're off to the Tempus Nebula
to gather chronitons.

03:06.354 --> 03:09.088
[ Sizzling ]

03:14.527 --> 03:16.963
Hey, Leela, look at me!

03:19.199 --> 03:22.270
[ Coughing, Wheezing ]

03:22.370 --> 03:25.438
Your face can take
a lot of punishment.
That's good to know.

03:25.538 --> 03:27.775
There's a lot about my face
you don't know.

03:27.875 --> 03:30.377
Perhaps you and it
could get better acquainted
over dinner.

03:30.478 --> 03:32.780
All right.
Cool your jets, hotshot.

03:32.879 --> 03:34.914
Come on, Leela.
Why won't you
go out with me?

03:35.014 --> 03:36.917
We both know
there's something there.

03:37.016 --> 03:40.420
No. I mean cool your jets.
They're melting Bender's face.

03:40.521 --> 03:43.156
Aaah! Ow, ow, ow!
Ooh! Aaah!

03:46.093 --> 03:48.829
Here you go.
Hot off the nebula.

03:48.929 --> 03:51.331
None too soon.
While you were gone,

03:51.432 --> 03:56.002
the Trotters held
a news conference to announce
that I was a jive sucker.

04:00.274 --> 04:02.509
[ Cooing ]

04:06.780 --> 04:08.748
[ Gasping ]

04:19.826 --> 04:23.331
Behold! My invincible
nuclear mutants!

04:23.430 --> 04:25.298
- Hi.
- Hello.

04:26.699 --> 04:29.870
Marv Albert here
at Madison Cube Garden...

04:29.970 --> 04:33.473
where the Harlem Globetrotters
take on a squad of atomic
supermen...

04:33.574 --> 04:36.709
in what promises
to be a by-the-numbers
athletic contest...

04:36.810 --> 04:38.846
with no surprises whatsoever.

04:40.314 --> 04:43.149
[ Whistle ]
There's the tip-off.
Globetrotter ball!

04:43.250 --> 04:47.153
Sweet Clyde Dixon
to Bubblegum Tate.
Drives down court.

04:47.254 --> 04:48.889
And Curly Joe from the rear!
[ Yelps ]

04:48.988 --> 04:51.992
[ Zoidberg Laughs ]
That one grabbed his behindus.

04:52.091 --> 04:55.963
- Shh!
- Who dares laugh
at the jesters of dunk?

04:56.062 --> 04:58.865
We came to terrify
and humiliate you,

04:58.966 --> 05:00.968
not tickle
your funny bones.

05:01.067 --> 05:03.670
Watch as I embarrass
your civilization...

05:03.771 --> 05:06.005
by passing the ball
to Curly Joe...

05:07.875 --> 05:11.177
only to have it
remain in my hands
with elastic!

05:11.278 --> 05:16.048
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Crowd Booing ]

05:16.149 --> 05:19.720
And perhaps this
will wipe the smiles
from your faces.

05:21.053 --> 05:23.923
[ Albert ]
Goose goes up! Rejected!

05:24.024 --> 05:27.694
- Growtreant
from half court. Yes!
- [ Cheering ]

05:29.562 --> 05:31.499
[ Crowd Cheering ]

05:31.598 --> 05:34.000
[ Albert ]
Supermen lead, 45-42.

05:34.100 --> 05:36.103
Arachneon with the steal,
to Thorias.

05:36.202 --> 05:38.672
Thorias from downtown.

05:38.771 --> 05:44.411
Yes! He's really showing us
what a man with a cannon
in his chest can do.

05:44.512 --> 05:47.680
No showboating,
you atomic hot dog!

05:47.781 --> 05:50.350
[ Grunting ]

05:50.451 --> 05:54.187
[ Buzzer ]
[ Albert ] And that's the half
with the Supermen up, 48-42.

05:54.286 --> 05:56.524
Surprisingly dull so far.

06:03.396 --> 06:06.298
Bubblegum, the Trotters
are down by six. Reactions?

06:06.399 --> 06:09.136
It was always our plan
to trail at the half,

06:09.235 --> 06:11.639
thus deepening
Earth's eventual humiliation.

06:11.738 --> 06:14.641
Also, what game
were the refs watching?

06:14.742 --> 06:16.709
[ Whistle ]

06:16.810 --> 06:18.812
[ Giggling ]

06:18.911 --> 06:21.449
[ Albert ]
Curly Joe, easily amused
by his own antics,

06:21.548 --> 06:23.483
continues to wreak havoc--

06:24.918 --> 06:26.819
[ Albert ]
What the--
Hey, man.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.822
Whoo!
What was that?

06:28.922 --> 06:33.661
Did everything just jump around
or did my brain just stroke off
there for a second?

06:33.761 --> 06:37.163
Ladies and gentlemen,
something very strange
has just happened...

06:37.264 --> 06:41.334
in this basketball game
between space clowns
and atomic monsters.

06:41.435 --> 06:43.504
Hmm?

06:49.810 --> 06:52.680
- Time out! Time out!
- [ Whistle ]

06:52.779 --> 06:56.649
- What's happening?
- We seem to be lurching forward
randomly in time,

06:56.750 --> 06:59.151
like a needle skipping
on a record player.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.754
What's causing it?
Is it my outfit?

07:01.855 --> 07:04.824
No. It must have
something to do with
those time particles...

07:04.925 --> 07:06.826
I used to
grow the supermen.

07:06.927 --> 07:10.531
Time and space
are ripping apart
at the seams.

07:10.630 --> 07:12.199
[ Gasping ]

07:13.500 --> 07:15.468
- Oops.
- Oh, great.

07:15.569 --> 07:18.672
Now, on top of everything,
we need a new fifth man.

07:18.771 --> 07:20.707
Ooh! Ooh, ooh, ooh!
Put me in, Professor!

07:20.807 --> 07:22.709
I wanna show Leela my skills.

07:22.810 --> 07:26.045
Hmm. Will said skills
pay the bills?

07:26.146 --> 07:29.115
Who cares?
We're 35 points ahead
with two minutes left.

07:29.216 --> 07:32.151
- What could possibly--
- [ Crowd Booing ]

07:35.055 --> 07:39.358
[ Buzzer ]
[ Albert ]
Globetrotters win, 244-86.

07:39.459 --> 07:41.461
A dark day for humanity, folks.

07:41.562 --> 07:45.499
We have been beaten...
in basketball.

07:45.598 --> 07:48.668
Yeah,
that's how we do it!
[ Laughing ]

07:48.769 --> 07:51.504
You are all fools
of the highest caliber.

07:51.605 --> 07:54.975
I don't know what you did,
Fry, but once again,
you screwed up.

07:55.074 --> 07:58.512
Now all the planets
are gonna start crackin' wise
about our mamas.

07:58.612 --> 08:02.382
I'm just glad my fat ugly mama
isn't alive to see this day.

08:02.482 --> 08:04.851
Enough about your
promiscuous mother,
Hermes.

08:04.951 --> 08:06.853
We have
bigger problems.

08:06.954 --> 08:09.656
This time disruption
is extremely serious.

08:09.757 --> 08:13.060
Damn right, brother man.
This chronological
wang-dang-doodle...

08:13.160 --> 08:15.194
could destroy
the very matrix of reality.

08:15.295 --> 08:19.365
Tate, what do you know
about this?
Not much yet,

08:19.466 --> 08:24.271
but I am senior lecturer in
physics at Globetrotter "U" and
I'd like to help investigate.

08:24.370 --> 08:26.505
You're that Bubblegum Tate?

08:26.606 --> 08:30.009
Well, I sure ain't his grandma.
Now, look here, Prof.

08:30.110 --> 08:34.246
I think we got ourselves
an excess of chronitons
in the subatomic interstices.

08:34.346 --> 08:36.448
Yes. I see.

08:36.549 --> 08:41.388
Something involving
that many big words could
easily destabilize time itself.

08:41.488 --> 08:43.691
- Is that a problem?
- Indeed so.

08:43.790 --> 08:46.192
At this rate, by Tuesday
it will be Thursday.

08:46.293 --> 08:48.195
By Wednesday,
it will be August.

08:48.294 --> 08:51.731
And by Thursday,
it will be the end of
existence as we know it.

08:52.865 --> 08:54.802
I'll have to ask you
to clear out now.

08:54.902 --> 08:57.070
The circus needs to
set up for tomorrow's big--

08:57.169 --> 08:59.072
[ Trumpeting ]

08:59.172 --> 09:01.609
[ All Screaming ]

09:06.245 --> 09:10.082
Time continues
to skip forward randomly.
Details at 11:00.

09:10.182 --> 09:13.953
This is the news at 11:00.
The mysterious and unexplained--

09:14.053 --> 09:18.490
Turning to entertainment news,
teen singer Wendy might just be
the latest--

09:18.591 --> 09:20.559
Won three Grammys
last night--

09:20.661 --> 09:22.830
Found dead
in her bathtub.

09:22.929 --> 09:27.333
Interesting. It's as if
we all behave normally
during the time skips,

09:27.433 --> 09:29.336
but then
we have no memory of it.

09:29.436 --> 09:31.605
- You mean we just--
- My, yes!

09:31.705 --> 09:34.841
Ooh! Just like that.
Any luck, Bubblegum?

09:34.942 --> 09:36.844
Not yet. Listen.

09:36.943 --> 09:38.946
Hope you don't mind
if I dribble a little
while I work.

09:39.046 --> 09:42.615
Not if you'll grant me
the same liberty.
[ Slurps ]

09:42.716 --> 09:45.251
Ooh, ooh. Bubblegum,
my name's Bender,

09:45.351 --> 09:48.488
and I'm a huge fan of your work,
both on and off the court.

09:48.587 --> 09:51.323
Can I be
a Globetrotter?
Shut up, turkey.

09:51.423 --> 09:54.326
Ooh.
Bubblegum,
look at this.

09:54.427 --> 09:58.097
[ Clicking ]
The background time radiation
is fluctuating wildly!

09:58.197 --> 10:02.501
Good Lord!
That sucker's shakin' round
like some fine imported booty!

10:02.601 --> 10:07.274
Say, I'm no physicist,
but I think I know how to
stop the skipping. We'll just--

10:07.374 --> 10:10.711
** [ Calypso ]

10:10.811 --> 10:13.046
I don't know how
this was supposed to work.

10:13.145 --> 10:16.884
Professor, I hope you find out
what's wrong before we skip
right past my birth--

10:16.984 --> 10:18.551
Happy birthday, Amy!

10:18.652 --> 10:21.321
Hooray! Look at
all these presents!

10:21.421 --> 10:24.356
I hope we all have as much fun
tomorrow at my birth--

10:24.456 --> 10:28.327
What? Awww.

10:30.197 --> 10:33.667
Psst. Leela! I've set up
a time-proof shelter
in the closet.

10:33.767 --> 10:36.536
There's only room for two,
and you're the one I want to
share it with.

10:36.635 --> 10:39.505
Fry, that's so sweet.
Lemme see.

10:43.811 --> 10:46.913
How exactly
will this protect us
from time jumps?

10:47.014 --> 10:50.984
'Cause when we're
together in here, baby,
time will stand still.

10:51.084 --> 10:52.552
Owww.

10:54.520 --> 10:57.190
Hmm. Hmm.

11:00.059 --> 11:02.895
Dr. Zoidberg,
can I talk to you
about Fry?

11:02.995 --> 11:04.998
Leela,
I would be honored.

11:05.097 --> 11:08.836
** [ Action Theme ]
Does the worst W.C. Fields
imitation I've ever seen.

11:08.936 --> 11:12.773
Zoidberg!
Sorry. You must've
been boring me.

11:12.873 --> 11:17.177
[ TV Stops ]
The thing is, Fry is very sweet,
but he's so immature.

11:17.277 --> 11:21.014
I love his boyish charm,
but I hate his childishness.

11:21.114 --> 11:26.586
So he's not perfect.
You don't wanna end up
old and lonely like Zoidberg.

11:26.686 --> 11:29.556
[ Sobbing ]

11:29.655 --> 11:31.691
[ Sniffles ]
You were saying?

11:31.792 --> 11:33.927
[ Sniffing ]

11:34.027 --> 11:37.029
Ah! There it is.
The Tempus Nebula.

11:37.129 --> 11:39.131
Take a whiff
through the Smell-A-Scope.

11:41.701 --> 11:43.803
Ooh!
What's that funky jazz?

11:43.903 --> 11:46.572
The odor
of pure time leaking.

11:46.673 --> 11:48.741
When my crew
removed the chronitons,

11:48.841 --> 11:50.744
it destabilized
the nebula,

11:50.844 --> 11:53.279
causing time skips
throughout the universe.

11:53.379 --> 11:55.315
Ooh! Let Bubblegum
tell it!

11:55.414 --> 11:58.951
Pretend these basketballs
are time particles,
my silver honky.

11:59.052 --> 12:02.654
As the nebula
bounce-passes them off us...
Aaah! Ooh! Aaah!

12:02.755 --> 12:05.591
they cause these dents,
or "time skips."

12:05.692 --> 12:07.794
You are so smart.

12:07.894 --> 12:10.831
Hold up.
What if we were to move
this cluster of stars...

12:10.931 --> 12:13.299
to these
algebraic coordinates?

12:13.399 --> 12:16.102
Their gravity might just
divert the chronitons...

12:16.202 --> 12:18.171
to the empty side
of the universe.

12:18.270 --> 12:20.673
Yeah. But it's impossible.

12:20.774 --> 12:23.811
Moving stars would require
one bad-ass gravity pump.

12:23.911 --> 12:25.913
And we'd need all the money
on Earth to build--

12:26.013 --> 12:28.014
What the--
What?

12:29.515 --> 12:31.784
There's the funding
for your gravity pump.

12:31.884 --> 12:36.088
But it damn well better work.
We can't spend all of Earth's
money every day.

12:36.188 --> 12:38.290
Now, how long
will it take to build?

12:38.390 --> 12:42.695
It won't be easy, Nixon.
A jim-jam this complex
might take months or even--

12:42.796 --> 12:44.965
Ah. There we are.

12:45.065 --> 12:49.668
One gravity pump powerful enough
to move the stars themselves.

12:49.769 --> 12:53.673
Now to begin the arduous task
of attaching it to the ship so--

12:56.143 --> 12:58.044
Off you go, apparently.

13:04.183 --> 13:08.020
[ Tate ] Easy, Leela.
Just finger-roll that star
into the cosmic basket.

13:09.022 --> 13:11.825
Just a few... more...

13:11.924 --> 13:16.296
hundred...
thousand... miles.

13:16.395 --> 13:18.331
There.

13:21.869 --> 13:23.836
[ Tate ]
Nothin' but nebula.

13:23.937 --> 13:26.072
[ Clicking ]
We'll have to run some tests
back on Earth,

13:26.173 --> 13:28.207
but I think we've
stopped the time skips.

13:28.307 --> 13:30.543
All right!
Jammin'!
Hooray for Leela!

13:30.643 --> 13:32.846
And what better way
to celebrate our success...

13:32.946 --> 13:36.816
than by me showing Bubblegum
the Globetrotter uniform
I made myself?

13:36.917 --> 13:39.485
Lemme see.

13:39.586 --> 13:41.020
Hello, lawsuit.

13:41.120 --> 13:43.023
Leela,
I want you to know...

13:43.123 --> 13:46.225
I think the way
you moved those stars around
was really wonderful.

13:46.326 --> 13:48.227
I got you something.

13:48.327 --> 13:53.533
[ Gasps ] Moderately priced
domestic non-vintage champagne!
How did you know?

13:53.633 --> 13:58.171
You deserve it. I mean,
nobody ever stops to tell you
what a great captain you are.

13:58.270 --> 14:01.008
Aw. That is so true
and sweet.

14:01.107 --> 14:03.009
You're smart,
you're beautiful,

14:03.110 --> 14:05.577
and best of all,
you'll go out with me?

14:05.677 --> 14:08.681
Fry, please
try to understand.

14:08.780 --> 14:12.184
You're a man. I'm a woman.
We're just too different.

14:12.284 --> 14:17.190
Hey, Leela! Bubblegum might
let me organize a bake sale
for the Globetrotter wives.

14:17.289 --> 14:19.359
Can you teach me
to make cupcakes?

14:19.458 --> 14:22.595
All right, but I wanna
lick the beaters.
[ Sighs ]

14:22.695 --> 14:24.730
I got her champagne.
I opened it.

14:24.831 --> 14:26.698
What does a guy
have to do?

14:26.798 --> 14:28.969
Eighty-six the chump stuff,
F-man.

14:29.068 --> 14:34.240
It's time to win Leela's heart
with a big, showy, three-point
romantic gesture.

14:34.341 --> 14:38.644
Hmm. Maybe this is the moment
to show her my real surprise.

14:40.580 --> 14:42.481
[ Rockets Roaring ]

14:42.581 --> 14:44.985
Fry,
what are you doing?

14:45.085 --> 14:48.620
Uh-oh. Time to boogie on down
to the sauna.

14:48.721 --> 14:51.258
Look. I've been studying
how to pilot the ship.

14:51.357 --> 14:53.994
Impressed?
Yeah, actually.

14:54.094 --> 14:57.496
You're doing okay.
The core-reactor
temperature's nominal.

14:57.596 --> 15:00.466
The blinker's off.
I learned how to work
the gravity pump, too,

15:00.567 --> 15:02.501
in case we need to
move more stars.

15:02.601 --> 15:04.671
- So, are we dating now?
- [ Groans ]

15:04.770 --> 15:08.441
Is that what this is all about?
Please, just cut it out now.

15:08.541 --> 15:13.312
Look, Leela. I know there's
some perfect, amazing thing
I can do to make you love me.

15:13.413 --> 15:16.149
- And when I figure out
what it is--
- Fry, stop.

15:16.249 --> 15:20.352
I don't wanna hurt you,
but there is absolutely,
positively no way...

15:20.452 --> 15:23.090
that you and I
will ever, ever--

15:23.190 --> 15:26.658
Man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

15:26.759 --> 15:28.827
Mmm!
[ Groans ]

15:28.927 --> 15:31.965
- [ Cheering ]
- Yes!

15:36.036 --> 15:37.769
[ Grunting ]
[ Cheering ]

15:37.870 --> 15:39.772
[ Zoidberg ]
He looks radiant.

15:39.871 --> 15:43.176
- [ Muffled Speech ]
- Ye gods, Bubblegum! We failed.

15:43.275 --> 15:45.345
The time skips
haven't stopped at all.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.880
Even in these formal shorts,
I feel like a failure.

15:48.981 --> 15:52.652
You tricked me into
marrying you, didn't you?
Of course not!

15:52.751 --> 15:55.554
How'd you do it?
Drugs in the champagne?
Hypnosis?

15:55.654 --> 15:57.823
No! Drugs are for losers!

15:57.923 --> 16:00.692
And hypnosis is for losers
with big weird eyebrows.

16:00.793 --> 16:03.830
I don't know what amazing thing
I did to make you love me,

16:03.929 --> 16:06.232
but whatever it was,
we're married now.

16:06.332 --> 16:08.168
We've got the rest
of our lives to work this--

16:08.268 --> 16:10.970
Divorce is final.
What?

16:11.071 --> 16:13.005
Well, let's divide up
the china.

16:13.105 --> 16:17.344
I guess
I'll take the NFC helmets and
you can have the AFC helmets.

16:17.443 --> 16:20.013
Fine.
Break my heart again.

16:20.113 --> 16:22.649
Don't be so hard
on yourself, Fry.

16:22.749 --> 16:24.650
You lost the woman
of your dreams,

16:24.750 --> 16:26.686
but you still
have Zoidberg.

16:26.786 --> 16:29.022
You all
still have Zoidberg!

16:29.121 --> 16:33.860
How did I do it?
How did I get Leela to love me?
I've got to figure it out.

16:33.960 --> 16:36.328
Maybe you're just
a fantastic lover, Fry.

16:36.428 --> 16:38.164
No.
I don't know
what I'm doing.

16:38.264 --> 16:41.500
Maybe she'd come back to you
if your best friend Bender
were a Globetrotter.

16:41.600 --> 16:43.669
What do you say,
Bubblegum?
Hell no.

16:43.769 --> 16:46.673
- Awww.
- Oh, it's hopeless.

16:46.773 --> 16:49.676
I did something so great
that it won Leela's heart,

16:49.775 --> 16:52.078
and I'll never ever
know what it was.

16:52.178 --> 16:55.048
My life is empty.
[ Sniffles ]

16:55.148 --> 16:57.549
* Zoidberg

16:57.649 --> 17:00.452
No wonder we failed
to stop the time skips.

17:00.552 --> 17:03.855
Diverting chronitons
is mathematically impossible.

17:03.956 --> 17:08.095
I knew I should've checked
your showboating Globetrotter
algebra.

17:08.194 --> 17:11.364
Man, I thought you knew
that algebra was all razzmatazz!

17:11.463 --> 17:15.034
A Globetrotter
always saves the good algebra
for the final minutes.

17:15.134 --> 17:17.869
[ Bender Laughs ]
Vintage Bubblegum!

17:17.970 --> 17:20.106
The time skips
are worse than ever now.

17:20.207 --> 17:24.076
Isolated spots are jumping
by years at a time. Look!

17:24.176 --> 17:26.145
Stupid senior citizens.

17:26.246 --> 17:29.215
Why should we have to pay
for their Social Security
benefits?

17:29.316 --> 17:31.750
I deserve
free money!

17:31.851 --> 17:33.885
Well, I'm stumped.

17:33.986 --> 17:37.423
We'll have to call in
the finest scientific minds
in the univer--

17:37.523 --> 17:41.661
Perhaps we could explode
the whole damned nebula.

17:41.760 --> 17:44.663
What do you think,
Curly Joe?
No, man.

17:44.763 --> 17:48.934
An explosion big enough
to destroy that mama would
take out half the universe.

17:49.035 --> 17:52.003
You gotta Globetrotter
that explosion up a little,
Farnsie.

17:52.105 --> 17:54.273
Make it an implosion.

17:54.374 --> 17:56.808
By God,
Sweet Clyde is right!

17:56.909 --> 17:59.679
An implosion might just
form a black hole...

17:59.778 --> 18:02.315
that would stop
more chronitons from escaping.

18:02.414 --> 18:05.585
Whoa! Slow that
brain train down, Prof!

18:05.684 --> 18:09.020
We'd need some kind of
doomsday device to initiate
an implosion like that.

18:09.122 --> 18:11.022
Doomsday device?

18:11.124 --> 18:15.528
Ahh! Now the ball's
in Farnsworth's court!

18:18.597 --> 18:22.000
[ Beeping ]
I suppose I could part with one
and still be feared.

18:22.101 --> 18:24.002
Gimme some skin, Prof.

18:24.103 --> 18:26.173
I'm making you
an honorary Globetrotter.

18:26.272 --> 18:30.009
In fact,
everybody in this room's
an honorary Globetrotter.

18:30.108 --> 18:32.044
Yay!
I'm a Globetrotter!

18:32.144 --> 18:33.145
[ Hurried Footsteps ]

18:33.246 --> 18:34.980
[ Panting ]
Did you just say--

18:35.080 --> 18:37.683
- Too late, hot plate.
- Aw, crap!

18:37.784 --> 18:39.618
[ Beeping ]

18:42.822 --> 18:45.557
We must leave now,
for we are needed elsewhere.

18:45.657 --> 18:47.993
But we wish you
Godspeed.

18:49.895 --> 18:52.499
Please! Please let me
come with you.

18:52.598 --> 18:54.701
I can make myself
taller.

18:56.169 --> 18:59.038
Bender, you can talk trash.
You can handle the ball.

18:59.137 --> 19:01.340
But look in your heart
and ask yourself,

19:01.441 --> 19:04.344
are you funky enough
to be a Globetrotter?

19:04.443 --> 19:06.679
Are you?
Yes.

19:06.778 --> 19:10.682
Are you?
I mean, with time,
my funk level could--

19:10.782 --> 19:13.420
Are you?
[ Whimpers ]
No.

19:13.519 --> 19:15.988
Deal with it.

19:16.087 --> 19:18.224
[ Sniffling ]

19:21.260 --> 19:24.263
[ Beeping ]

19:31.938 --> 19:35.907
- Aaah! Oh!
- Careful with that
doomsday device, Bender.

19:36.008 --> 19:39.010
What does it matter?
I'll never be a Globetrotter.

19:39.111 --> 19:42.949
My life, and by extension
everyone else's, is meaningless.

19:43.048 --> 19:45.017
Roger.

19:45.116 --> 19:47.019
Leela,
about the wedding--

19:47.118 --> 19:49.087
I don't know what I did
to make you love me,

19:49.188 --> 19:52.358
and I don't think
I tricked you into it,
but maybe I did.

19:52.459 --> 19:54.861
And if I did,
I'm sorry.

19:54.961 --> 19:58.865
It's okay, Fry. You know
we'll always be friends,
right?

19:58.964 --> 20:01.567
Yeah, but I don't guess
anything I could do...

20:01.667 --> 20:04.770
will ever make you feel
the same way about me
that I do about you.

20:04.871 --> 20:07.105
I guess not.

20:10.376 --> 20:13.045
Well, the doomsday device
is ready.

20:13.144 --> 20:15.382
Maybe blasting
this quadrant of space...

20:15.481 --> 20:18.984
into a hellstorm
of flaming nothingness
will cheer me up a little.

20:19.085 --> 20:22.221
Okay. Let me just
take the ship out
to a safe distance.

20:24.490 --> 20:28.160
Actually,
I think I'll go down
and prep the detonator.

20:28.260 --> 20:30.896
Fry, why don't you
take the helm?

20:35.567 --> 20:38.837
She's so great.
I feel like I can
almost remember...

20:38.938 --> 20:41.173
the magical thing
I did to make her love me.

20:41.273 --> 20:43.174
But I guess
I never will.

20:43.276 --> 20:48.647
Sorry, buddy. I, too,
know what it's like to have
a dream I'll never achieve.

20:48.748 --> 20:52.684
** [ Slowly Whistling
"Sweet Georgia Brown" ]

20:54.019 --> 20:56.323
[ Engines Whirring ]

21:01.361 --> 21:02.929
Ohh!

21:10.369 --> 21:12.338
That's how I must've done it!

21:12.439 --> 21:16.509
I moved the stars themselves
to write her a love note
in the sky!

21:16.608 --> 21:20.046
[ Leela ]
Detonation in three, two, one.

21:20.145 --> 21:23.715
No!

21:32.358 --> 21:35.161
Did you see it?
Did you see it?

21:35.260 --> 21:38.130
- The explosion?
- No, not the explosion!

21:38.230 --> 21:42.335
- Then what?
- Nothing.

21:44.302 --> 21:48.307
** [ Bender Slowly Whistling
"Sweet Georgia Brown" ]
